The Hawks obtained a warrant of arrest for the pair. PRETORIA - Businesswoman, Pumza Ponshee Gambula, has been granted R20,000 bail. Gambula appeared briefly at the Specialised Commercial Crime Court in Mthatha on charges of fraud to the value of R5-million. It's alleged she charged three Eastern Cape municipalities for a COVID-19 door-to-door awareness campaign. READ: Hawks to make COVID-19 corruption related arrests Gambula's company allegedly submitted fraudulent documents to various councils. The Port St Johns, King Sabata Dalindyebo and Mhlonto local municipalities were targetted.